    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Electronic Control Systems Diagnostics - Circuit Diagnostics - VREF
        (Reference Voltage)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010706.36" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="4">
        <title>V
            <subscript>REF</subscript>
            (Reference Voltage)
        </title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s305010706.36.1">
            <figure id="f3050107171" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31223.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>Functional diagram for the V
                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <para id="s305010706.33.1.1"></para>
            <table id="t3050107345" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>The functional diagram for the V
                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                    includes the following:
                </title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Injection Control Pressure (ICP) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Barometric Absolute Pressure (BAP) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Accelerator Position Sensor and Idle Validation Switch (APS/IVS)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>The ECM contains a regulated 5 volt DC reference source to power engine and
                vehicle sensors. The signals are compared to the V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                to determine actual output signal values. These values are processed by the ECM for engine operation.
            </para>
            <para>The system has two V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                circuits:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>V
                        <subscript>REF</subscript>A for engine sensors
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>V
                        <subscript>REF</subscript>B for chassis sensors
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>See the applicable truck Circuit Diagram Manual for APS, and BAP sensor circuit diagrams.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.36.2">
            <title>V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                Circuit Operation
            </title>
            <figure id="f3050107172" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31224.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
                <caption>V
                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                    circuit diagram
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The ECM supplies V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                when ignition switch is on at Pins X1-14 (engine connector) and X4-4 (chassis connector).
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection/Management</title>There are no DTCs for V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>circuit. If a VREFcircuit fault such as an open, a short to ground, or a short
                to power (above 5 volts) occurs, multiple DTCs are set for each sensor not getting the correct VREF
                value. If a circuit fault such as an open or a short to power on signal ground occurs, multiple DTCs are
                set for each sensor not getting the correct ground. One sensor having an internal short (VREFshorted to
                signal ground could cause this condition). The sensors affected is dependent upon where the open or
                short is located.
            </para>
            <para>When the ECM sets multiple sensor DTCs, the V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                circuit is open or shorted, or the signal ground circuit is open. To determine if the V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                circuits are the cause, complete the pin-point diagnostics check.
            </para>
            <table id="t3050107346" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Tools</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>EST with MasterDiagnostics&#174; software</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>EZ-Tech&#174; interface cable</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Digital Multimeter (DMM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Breakout harnesses</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Breakout Box</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Terminal Test Adapter Kit</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>After removing connector, inspect for damaged pins, corrosion, or loose terminals. Repair as
                        required.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.36.3">
            <title>V
                <subscript>REF</subscript>
                Pin-Point Diagnostics
            </title>
            <figure id="f3050107173" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31224.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
                <caption>V
                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                    circuit diagram
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t3050107347" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Voltage Checks - Connector</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.71*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.77*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.58*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col4" colwidth="2.03*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col4" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>If multiple DTCs are set, remove harness connections. Connect breakout harness.
                                    Turn ignition switch to ON, do not crank the engine. Measure V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    at suspected sensor circuits.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col4" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>MAP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5 &#177; 0.5 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry morerows="3">
                                <para>Check V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    at each sensor. To isolate area of short or open circuit, identify sensors without V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    and sensors that share a common V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>. If disconnecting a sensor causes V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    to be present in the circuit that had no previous V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>, it is likely that the disconnected sensor had shorted V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>ICP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5 &#177; 0.5 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>APS/IVS</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>(C for CF or D for stripped chassis) to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5 &#177; 0.5 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>BAP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>5 &#177; 0.5 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para></para>
            <table id="t3050107348" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Resistance Checks - Connector to Chassis Ground</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.71*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.77*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.58*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col4" colwidth="2.03*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col4" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <warning>
                                    <para>To avoid personal injury, death, including damage to the engine or vehicle,
                                        always disconnect main negative battery cable first. Always connect the main
                                        negative battery cable last.
                                    </para>
                                </warning>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch to OFF. Disconnect harness from sensors using VREF.
                                    Disconnect negative battery cable.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col4" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>MAP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>> 500 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry morerows="3">
                                <para>If resistance is less than specification, check for short to ground. If a short to
                                    ground condition exists, remove all sensor connectors that are connected to V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    and ECM. Inspect to determine if short is in sensor, ECM, or wiring harness.
                                    Specification is > 1 k&#x2126; with all common sensors disconnected from harness.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>ICP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>> 500 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>APS/IVS</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>(C for CF or D for stripped chassis) to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>> 1 k&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>BAP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>> 1 k&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t3050107349" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Harness Resistance Checks - VREF to ECM</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.71*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.77*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.58*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col4" colwidth="2.03*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col4" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch and all accessories to OFF. Disconnect harness from sensors
                                    using VREF. Connect breakout harness to harness only. Connect Breakout Box to
                                    harness only.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col4" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>MAP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to X1-14</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry morerows="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance with DMM from sensor connector to ECM 24-pin connectors. If
                                    resistance is greater than 5 &#x2126;, check for high resistance or an open in the V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    supply circuit.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>ICP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to X1-14</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>APS/IVS</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>(C for CF or D for stripped chassis) to X4-4</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>BAP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>2 to X4-4</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para></para>
            <figure id="f3050107174" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31224.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
                <caption>V
                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                    circuit diagram
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t3050107350" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Harness Resistance Checks - Signal Ground to ECM</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.71*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.77*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.58*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col4" colwidth="2.03*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col4" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <caution>
                                    <para>To avoid engine damage, turn ignition switch to OFF before unplugging the
                                        connector or relay for the ECM. Failure to turn ignition switch to OFF will
                                        cause a voltage spike and damage to electrical components.
                                    </para>
                                </caution>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch and all accessories to OFF. Disconnect harness from sensors
                                    using VREF. Connect breakout harness to harness only. Connect Breakout Box to engine
                                    harness only.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col4" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>MAP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1 to X1-6</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry morerows="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance with DMM from sensor connector to ECM 24-pin connectors. If
                                    resistance is greater than 5 &#x2126;, check for loose connection or open in signal
                                    ground circuit.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>ICP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1 to X1-6</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>APS/IVS</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>(B for CF or K for stripped chassis) to X4-24</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>BAP</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>1 to X4-24</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
